FRONTEND:
- have a separate route per page. If you refresh the page, you go back to the first page.
- Edit bank accounts => change the name of the bank account, mark them as internal.
- Edit labels.
- Remove labels.
- Link bank accounts to labels.
- Remove bank accounts from labels.

- Add a detail view from a label and a bank account. 

BACKEND

BANK ACCOUNTS:
- Don't normalize the bank account number. (e.g. "BE57063675847535" -> "BE57 0636 7584 7535").
- Be strict about the bank account properties. Numbers are persisted in the number column, names, in the name column. We don't switch those.
- Add a hash property to the bank account. It's a quick hash of the original bank account name concatenated with the number. This way, we can still link transfers with the old name to the bank account.
- Bank accounts don't have an owner.
- Add the ability to mark bank accounts as internal, can be done automatically (check amount and to or from account), and change the name of the bank account (patch endpoint)
- Return the total balance of the bank account. If it's in the to column, multiply by -1 before adding it to the balance. If it's in the from column, don't multiply by -1.'. We should add a balance column to the bank account entity and update it if new transfers are imported (but don't do that for a transfer from an internal account to an internal account).

LABELS:
- Return the total balance of the label. Here we can just take the amount of the transfers that are linked to the label. Update this if a label is updated or if transfers are imported.
- Labels don't have an owner.'
- Update labels => regex, linked bank accounts. max value, max percentage. If a label is updated, remove the label from all the transfers, if it's not manually added. And relink the label with the current transfers.

TRANSFERS:
- Transfers don't have an owner.'
- Change logic of isInternalTransfer => if the from and to bank accounts are marked as internal.
